VALUES	(	1	,'2020-12-15 03:01:01'	,1	,'2 h 25 m'	, 'In a small bowl, drain cherry juice and add rum set aside. Prepare vanilla and chocolate puddings in separate bowls, according to package directions. Allow to set up 5 minutes.**In a 9x13 inch baking dish, place a layer of cookies on the bottom of the dish cut a few of the cookies in order to create a tight fit, if needed.**Sprinkle cookie layer with 1/3 of the cherry juice mixture and spoon vanilla pudding over the cookies, spreading to the edge of the pan. Repeat steps with cookies, cherry juice and chocolate pudding. Make final layer with cookies and remaining juice.**In a medium bowl, whip cream and sugar together until soft peaks form. Top dessert with whipped cream, sprinkle with almonds, and garnish with whole cherries. Refrigerate for 2 hours or more before serving.**'	,'Zuppa Inglese Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/739892.jpg'	),
          (	2	,'2020-12-15 03:01:02'	,1	,'8 h 20 m'	, 'In a medium bowl, mix together grated zucchini, cilantro, lime juice, oil, salt, and sugar. Pack into a jar or resealable container and refrigerate overnight before serving.**'	,'Zucchini Relish Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/4540631.jpg'	),
          (	3	,'2020-12-15 03:01:03'	,1	,'1 h 15 m'	, 'In a medium bowl, mix cream cheese and milk until well blended. Mix in the zucchini, chives and salt. Chill in the refrigerator approximately 1 hour before serving.**'	,'Zucchini Chive Dip Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/21385.jpg'	),
          (	4	,'2020-12-15 03:01:04'	,1	,'13 h 35 m'	, 'Whisk together the olive oil, wine or sherry vinegar, shallot, parsley, basil, garlic, salt and pepper. Allow to refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator and serve at room temperature.**'	,'Zinfandel Vinaigrette Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/998762.jpg'	),
          (	5	,'2020-12-15 03:01:05'	,1	,'30 m'	, 'In a food processor or blender, combine onions, wine, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper.  Process until onions and garlic are pureed.  Add mayonnaise and blend until smooth.  Refrigerate until very cold, and whisk dressing just before serving.**'	,'Zinfandel Salad Or Slaw Dressing Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/260032.jpg'	),
          (	6	,'2020-12-15 03:01:06'	,1	,'1 m'	, 'Pour the malt liquor over ice in a tall glass. Stir in a shot of blackberry brandy.**'	,'Zima Plus Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/4556603.jpg'	),
          (	7	,'2020-12-15 03:01:07'	,1	,'5 m'	, 'Mash tuna in a small bowl with a fork.  Add mayonnaise, pickle relish, mustard, celery, onion, and black pepper stir to combine.  Chill and serve.**'	,'Zesty Tuna Salad Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/45363.jpg'	),
          (	8	,'2020-12-15 03:01:08'	,1	,'30 m'	, 'In a mixing bowl, combine the broccoli, cauliflower, onions and dressing. Toss, cover and refrigerate. Sprinkle with sunflower seeds before serving.**'	,'Zesty Broccoli and Cauliflower Salad Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/417313.jpg'	),
          (	9	,'2020-12-15 03:01:09'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'In a large bowl, mix together the barbeque sauce, steak sauce, beer, bourbon whiskey, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, seasoned salt, black pepper, dried onion, basil, oregano, habanero hot sauce, curry powder, red pepper flakes, and brown sugar.**Cover the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish with approximately 1/2 the marinade. Place desired meat in the dish, and cover with remaining mixture. Cover, and marinate in the refrigerator at least 6 hours before grilling as desired.**'	,'Zesty Barbeque Marinade Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/95438.jpg'	),
          (	10	,'2020-12-15 03:01:10'	,1	,'20 m'	, 'In a 12x12 inch or larger dish, evenly spread the refried beans in a thin layer.**In a medium bowl, mix the avocado and lemon juice until almost smooth. A few avocado lumps are desirable. Spread the avocado mixture over the refried beans.  In a medium bowl, blend the sour cream and taco seasoning spread over the avocado mixture. Sprinkle the tomatoes in a layer over the sour cream mixture, followed by the olives and the green onions. Top the dip with a layer of cheese.**'	,'Yummy Taco Salad Dip Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/6066765.jpg'	),
          (	11	,'2020-12-15 03:01:11'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'In a blender combine strawberries, ice, milk, ice cream and sugar. Blend until smooth**'	,'Yummy Strawberry Shake Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/4531794.jpg'	),
          (	12	,'2020-12-15 03:01:12'	,1	,'8 h 15 m'	, 'In a medium bowl, mix together chopped spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, green onions, dry vegetable dip mix, water chestnuts and prepared Dijon-style mustard. Chill in the refrigerator 8 hours, or overnight, before serving.**'	,'Yummy Spinach Dip Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/images/79591.png'	),
          (	13	,'2020-12-15 03:01:13'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'Lay the ham slices flat on a serving plate and pat dry. Spread with cream cheese. Place a pickle spear at one end of each slice, and roll the slices into cylinders around the spears secure with toothpicks.**'	,'Yummy Roll Ups Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/580486.jpg'	),
          (	14	,'2020-12-15 03:01:14'	,1	,'5 m'	, 'In a large punch bowl, pour 2 liters chilled cranberry ginger ale. Next scoop raspberry sherbet into bowl. Then pour the other 2 liters of chilled cranberry ginger ale over sherbet. Serve.**'	,'Yummy Pink Punch Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/2111755.jpg'	),
          (	15	,'2020-12-15 03:01:15'	,1	,'5 m'	, 'In a blender combine limeade, beer and tequila. Fill blender to the top with ice. Blend until thick and smooth.**Salt the rims of 2 large margarita glasses. To do so, pour salt onto a small plate, moisten the rims of the glasses on a damp towel and press them into the salt.**Serve the margaritas in the salted glasses and garnish with slices of lime.**'	,'Yummy Margaritas Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/199785.jpg'	),
          (	16	,'2020-12-15 03:01:16'	,1	,'4 h 15 m'	, 'In a large skillet fry the bacon. Remove the bacon from the skillet and drain on paper towels. Chop or break the cooled bacon into small pieces.**In a medium-size mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, bacon, mayonnaise, and green onions. When mixed well, form 2 balls out of the mixture. Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, or overnight.**Before serving, roll the cheese balls in the chopped pecans.**'	,'Yummy Cheese Ball Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/755555.jpg'	),
          (	17	,'2020-12-15 03:01:17'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'In a medium bowl, mix together spinach, plain yogurt, mayonnaise, seasoning salt, parsley, basil, oregano, dry mustard and garlic salt. Chill until serving.**'	,'Yogurt Spinach Dip Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/1114534.jpg'	),
          (	18	,'2020-12-15 03:01:18'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'In a small bowl, beat together yogurt and lemon juice until smooth. Stir in mustard, parsley, and chives. Refrigerate until ready to serve.**'	,'Yogurt Salad Dressing Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/474853.jpg'	),
          (	19	,'2020-12-15 03:01:19'	,1	,'2 h 10 m'	, 'Prepare drink mix according to package directions. Combine with yogurt. Pour into ice pop molds and freeze until firm.**'	,'Yogurt Pops Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/856385.jpg'	),
          (	20	,'2020-12-15 03:01:20'	,1	,'3 m'	, 'In a small bowl or blender, stir together the yogurt, chopped mint, sugar, salt and cayenne until well blended. Serve immediately or chill for a while to let the flavors come together.**'	,'Yogurt Mint Sauce Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/3277211.jpg'	),
          (	21	,'2020-12-15 03:01:21'	,1	,'2 h 5 m'	, 'In a medium-size mixing or serving bowl, combine yogurt, sour cream, parsley, cilantro, green onion, and celery salt. Mix well, cover, and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.**'	,'Yogurt Herb Dipping Sauce Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/965976.jpg'	),
          (	22	,'2020-12-15 03:01:22'	,1	,'5 m'	, 'In a small bowl, combine yogurt, brown sugar and lemon juice. Stir until smooth and spread on cooled cake.**'	,'Yogurt Glaze Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/1438277.jpg'	),
          (	23	,'2020-12-15 03:01:23'	,1	,'50 m'	, 'Combine evaporated milk, sugar and vanilla. Freeze in an ice cream maker according to manufacturers instructions.**'	,'Worry Free Ice Cream Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/4559048.jpg'	),
          (	24	,'2020-12-15 03:01:24'	,1	,'3 m'	, 'Fill cocktail shaker with fresh ice cubes. Add about 1/2 ounce each dry and sweet vermouth.  Shake enough to coat ice and pour off liquid.  Add eight ounces gin to coated ice in shaker and shake vigorously.  Pour into four chilled Martini glasses, garnish with pimiento-stuffed olive and serve.**'	,'Worlds Greatest Martini Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/610111.jpg'	),
          (	25	,'2020-12-15 03:01:25'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese, crushed pineapple, onion powder and garlic. Mix in reserved juice from pineapple as desired. Chill in the refrigerator until serving.**'	,'Worlds Best Cream Cheese and Pineapple Dip Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/4518834.jpg'	),
          (	26	,'2020-12-15 03:01:26'	,1	,'30 m'	, 'In a medium bowl, beat the egg. Mix in the water.**In a large bowl, combine the flour and salt. Create a well in the center of the mixture and slowly pour in the egg and water. Mix well. If the mixture is too dry, increase the amount of water one teaspoon at a time until a pliable dough has formed.**On a lightly floured surface, knead the dough until elastic. Cut dough into two separate balls. Cover the balls with a damp cloth for a minimum of 10 minutes.**Cut each ball into four equal pieces. Roll the pieces into 10 1/2 by 10 1/2 inch squares. Cut each into nine 3 1/2 by 3 1/2 inch squares. Use in any recipe that calls for wonton wrappers.**'	,'Wonton Wrappers Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/1092172.jpg'	),
          (	27	,'2020-12-15 03:01:27'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'In a large bowl, toss together the salad greens, cranberries, sunflower seeds and tomatoes.  Top with avocado (and chicken strips, if desired), add vinaigrette and serve.**'	,'Wonderful Raspberry Walnut Dinner Salad Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/1006670.jpg'	),
          (	28	,'2020-12-15 03:01:28'	,1	,'15 m'	, 'Empty the limeade into a 2 quart pitcher. Using the empty limeade cans, fill each one twice with citrus soda and pour into the pitcher. Fill one limeade can with tequila and pour into the pitcher. Adjust alcohol to personal taste. Mix well and serve.**'	,'Wonderful Margaritas Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/995411.jpg'	),
          (	29	,'2020-12-15 03:01:29'	,1	,'25 m'	, 'In a blender or food processor, combine sugar, lemon juice, onion, mustard, and salt. Process until well blended. With machine still running, add oil in a slow, steady stream until mixture is thick and smooth. Add poppy seeds, and process just a few seconds more to mix.**In a large serving bowl, toss together the romaine lettuce, shredded Swiss cheese, cashews, dried cranberries, apple, and pear. Pour dressing over salad just before serving, and toss to coat.**'	,'Winter Fruit Salad with Lemon Poppyseed Dressing Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/736393.jpg'	),
          (	30	,'2020-12-15 03:01:30'	,1	,'25 m'	, 'In a blender or food processor, combine sugar, lemon juice, onion, mustard, and salt. Process until well blended. With machine still running, add oil in a slow, steady stream until mixture is thick and smooth. Add poppy seeds, and process just a few seconds more to mix.**In a large serving bowl, toss together the romaine lettuce, shredded Swiss cheese, cashews, dried cranberries, apple, and pear. Pour dressing over salad just before serving, and toss to coat.**'	,'Winter Fruit Salad with Lemon Poppyseed Dressing Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/736393.jpg'	),
          (	31	,'2020-12-15 03:01:31'	,1	,'10 m'	, 'Mix together soy sauce, wine, sugar, garlic, ginger and molasses.  Pour over meat and refrigerate.**'	,'Wine Marinade Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/250x250/470984.jpg'	),
          (	32	,'2020-12-15 03:01:32'	,1	,'5 m'	, 'In a medium-size mixing bowl, combine confectioners sugar with wine. Pour over cake while cake is still hot.**'	,'Wine Glaze Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/2833320.jpg'	),
          (	33	,'2020-12-15 03:01:33'	,1	,'1 h 30 m'	, 'In a pitcher, combine peach schnapps, cognac, sugar, sliced oranges and sliced mangos. Chill for at least an hour.**Pour fruit mixture into a large punch bowl. Stir in white wine and ginger ale.**'	,'White Sangria Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/1031312.jpg'	),
          (	34	,'2020-12-15 03:01:34'	,1	,'2 h 10 m'	, 'In a large pitcher, combine dry white wine, peach vodka, lemonade concentrate and sugar. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add sliced peaches, red and green grapes.**Refrigerate sangria until well chilled, at least 2 hours, or overnight to blend flavors. Serve over ice, and use a slotted spoon to include sliced peaches and grapes with each serving.**'	,'White Peach Sangria Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/417474.jpg'	),
          (	35	,'2020-12-15 03:01:35'	,1	,'3 h'	, 'Sprinkle gelatin over cold water set aside to soften.**Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour, and salt in a saucepan. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over low heat, stirring until it boils. Boil for 1 minute, and remove from heat. Transfer to a large bowl. Stir in softened gelatin. When partially set, beat with a rotary mixer until smooth. Blend in vanilla and 1 cup coconut.**Whip the cream until stiff. Gently fold into coconut mixture.**In a clean bowl, beat egg whites until frothy. Beat in cream of tartar and 1/2 cup sugar. Continue beating until egg whites form stiff peaks. Fold into coconut mixture. Pile filling into cooled pie shell. Sprinkle with additional coconut.  Chill pie for at least 2 hours or overnight.**'	,'White Christmas Pie Recipe '	,'https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/1083561.jpg'	),
